PRIVACY POLICY FOR ALL HAVOS MOBILE APPLICATIONS AND THE HAVOS WEBSITE
This privacy policy covers Your use of this Service. This page is used to inform visitors regarding our policies with the collection, use, and disclosure of Personal Information if anyone decides to use our Service.
This policy is effective as of
2020-04-18
If You choose to use our Service, then You agree to the collection and use of information in relation to this policy. The Personal Information that we collect is used for providing and improving the Service. We will not use or share Your information with anyone except as described in this Privacy Policy.
The terms used in this Privacy Policy have the same meanings as in our Terms and Conditions, which is accessible here:
Havos Terms and Conditions w.r.t. apps available on the Apple App Store
Havos Terms and Conditions w.r.t. apps available on Google Play
Havos Terms and Conditions w.r.t. apps available on the Amazon App Store
1. Personal Information Collected by Havos (not including third party services)
Havos itself collects very little personal information.
Those Havos Services
offering coins within the Service
for purchase of digital assets, such as games, gaming packs and hints, do connect to a central Havos administered server. The server creates a random anonymised username and password (which can be seen in the Service), not in anyway connected to Your real name or identity. You have the ability in the Service to change this username and password to one of Your choosing. This login is used to allow Havos to store the following information:
The language and country You set in the Service
The number of gaming coins You currently hold
The kinds of digital assets You have purchased in the Service, such as games, gaming packs, coins spent on hints
Any in-app purchases You have made, such as additional coins or a subscription to remove ads
Our Service can also collect the following information:
Any feedback You have provided about issues You have with clues/questions offered in the Service (again by connecting to the central Havos administered server)
Havos Limited retains Your e-mail address and e-mail contents if You have provided feedback regarding the Service via our e-mail feedback feature. We do not pass this e-mail or Your e-mail address on to any other party.
This list includes only the data collected and stored by Havos. Other kinds of data may be collected by third party services Havos uses. These are discussed in a later section of this privacy notice.
Note that Havos has
no information or knowledge of the actual identity of You, the user of this Service
. Our Service do NOT have access to or stores Your real first or last names or e-mail addresses, only the language and country You have set in the Service.
2. Use of This Information
Havos will use the information that we store on our centralized database server only for the following purposes:
Compile anonymous statistical data and analysis for use internally (e.g. how many gaming packs of a certain kind are purchased)
Create and manage Your account (e.g. remotely award additional coins You may have lost through a fault in the Service)
Fulfill and manage internal currency payments made with virtual coins
Increase the efficiency and operation of the Service
Prevent fraudulent transactions, and protect against criminal activity (e.g. our server checks with Apple App Store to ensure an in-app purchase is genuine)
Improve the quality of clues/questions provided in the Service
Provide an e-mail response to an e-mail You may have sent us via our e-mail feature
Troubleshoot problems
3. Disclosure of Your Information
We do not disclose this information to any other parties
4. Security of Your Information
We use administrative, technical, and physical security measures to help protect Your personal information.  While we have taken reasonable steps to secure the personal information You provide to us, please be aware that despite our efforts, no security measures are perfect or impenetrable, and no method of data transmission can be guaranteed against any interception or other type of misuse. Therefore, we cannot guarantee complete security.
5. Data Retention Policy, Managing Your Information
Havos will retain the information we collect, as listed above. However you can contact us using the contact information at the end of this policy at anytime and request that we delete all personal data we have collected, including any e-mails you have sent us, your e-mail address and the other listed information if you provide us with the username created in the Service.
6. Policy for Children
If You are less than the age of 18, You must obtain Your parent’s permission to access our site and to use our Services. If You are less than 13, You are not permitted to access the site, or to play any of our games or use any of our Services. This site and all of our games and Services are not intended for children below the age of 13 and we do not knowingly market to or collect, use or disclose information from children under the age of 13. If Havos Ltd learns that we have inadvertently gathered personal information from children under such age, Havos Ltd will take reasonable measures to promptly erase such personal information from our records. If You are a parent or guardian and You are aware that Your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so that we will be able to do delete the data. Our contact information is below.
7. Third Party services that may collect personal information
We want to inform You that this Service uses third parties that may have access to Your Personal Information. The reason is to perform the tasks assigned to them on our behalf. However, they are obligated not to disclose or use the information for any other purpose. We employ third-party companies for the following reasons:
To facilitate our Service.
To perform Service-related services.
To assist us in analyzing how our Service is used.
To assist us in diagnosing problems.
Here are links to the privacy policy of the third party service providers used by the Service:
Google Play Services
Apple App Store Services
Amazon App Store Services
AdMob (Advertizing service owned and administered by Google)
Ogury (Advertizing service)
Google Analytics for Firebase
Firebase Crashlytics
It is important to follow and read the information provided in each of these links to fully understand the kind of data collected by those third party service providers and how that data is used. This can include the collection of information that these third party services use to provide targeted advertizing.
Here follows a short summary regarding how Havos uses each of these services:
Google Play Services & Apple App Store Services
:  Used to provide in app purchases and centralised high score comparisons and achievements under an anonymised login system administered by Google or Apple
Amazon App Store Services
:  Used to provide centralised high score comparisons and achievements (GameCircle) under an anonymised login system administered entirely by Amazon
Admob & Ogury
:  Used to provide in-app advertizing, including targeted ads using collected personal information
Google Analytics for Firebase
:  Used to provide macro information about how our Services are used, e.g. how many total minutes across all players are spend playing a game and which game features are popular. This information is entirely anonymized and cannot be used to identify You, and provides very useful data to enable us to improve our Service
Firebase Crashlytics
:  Used to provide information regarding any crashes in our Service. This information is anonymous (only the type of device and OS version is known), in order for us to improve the quality of our Service
